participating-org.narrative: HIRDA is an acronym of Himilo Relief and development Association, a non-profit and non-political organisation founded by Somali refugees in the Netherlands in The Hague in 1998. The organisation#s purpose is to take part in the reconstruction and humanitarian effort in Somalia, promote basic education, gender mainstreaming, and encourage the integration and engagement in development among theSomali community in the Netherlands. HIRDA started its education support program in 1999 after the collapse of the education systemin Bardera city following the collapse of the Said Barre government in 1991. Since then HIRDA has been involved in other development activities in Gedo, Galgudud and other regions in southern Somalia. It is now engaged in education, health, relief distribution, support of orphans and the disabled, peace and human rights, women#s empowerment, water improvement and other projects in south and central Somalia. The projects in Somalia are being implemented by the Hirda Somalia office. Hirda Netherlands is responsible for fundraising in Western Europe and North America and for reporting to donor organisations.
